What are Ecocerts?


"Ecocerts are environmental hypercerts that standardize the measurement and representation of environmental impact. Within this standardized framework, environmental work and its associated impacts are clearly defined and quantified.


A core principle of ecocerts is non-duplication: if the impact of environmental work is represented in one ecocert, it cannot be included in or overlap with any other hypercert. This ensures that environmental impacts are not double-counted."

(https://gainforest.gitbook.io/docs/solutions/ecocerts)


